Q) What is kubernetes?
      => Kubernetes is a open-source orchastration and management tools for containers. (it's give the instruction to components to work together)
      => Developed by Google and written in Golang.
      => Containerized Orchestration System.
      => You can manage and do work like upgrade, manager, configure, scaling of containers from central location.
      => Provide Application Deployment, Scaling and Management on demand.

        Some other paid K8s cluster are also avalible:-
        ==============================================
        	a. EKS: Amazon Elastic K8s service.  (readymate kubernetes cluster manager by AWS)
        	b. GKE: Google k8s engine.
        	c. AKS: Azure k8s service.
        	d. microk8s: k8s for development.(free for local testing)

        	Note: All cloud have different platform but kubernetes functions are same.

Q) Advantages or Why we need K8s?
        1. Centerilized management
                => We can manage pods(containers) from central server(control-plane) and can do daily tasks like pod creation, deletion, upgradation, deployment, scalling of pods. etc.	        
	      
        2. Cluster (Failover).
                => If any workder node went down due to any reason, in that case all workload of (containers) will be failover(migrate) to on another node.
        
        3. Scalability: Increased containers numbers for running application as per demand.
	
							Scalability are two types(kubernetes support both types)
									a) Manually
									b) Automatically(you can set threshold like 85%)
	
							To perform scalability we have two mode.
									a) Vertical form   => To inscrease the resources like cpu, memory of existing containers.
									b) Horizental form => when you nedd to increase instances count of containers.
	
		4. Rollout and rollback.
				=> In kubernetes you can upgrade your application with zero downtime.
				=> rollback means you can back to old version if lastet version not compatable with application.

		6. Auto-mate Docker Deployment :- K8s can help you to manage automate the docker deployment.
		7. Auto-Healing : If a container is not healthy then K8s can auto replace, re-deploy, restart the container. It is now K8s responsibility.

Q) What is Statefulset?
   	=> Statefulset are kubernetes resource that allow us to deploy and manage stateful applications.
    
    	Stateful Applications : Applications that required presistence storage to run applications. like (Database applications)
    	Stateless Applications : Applications which do not required pv storage to run applications. (web server)

