	There are 4 services which running on master node.
	1) kube-api: api means listen: 
			=> It does validata (authentication and autherization) of any instructions which giving by kubernetes administrator.
				 (means check the roles and user rights, do they have right to execute the command and working area of user.)
			=> It is responsible to perform every action within the cluster.
	     	=> if api went down then existing workload would be down.	
	2) kube-etcd
			=> It is the k8s database which containes api related information or contain complete cluster information. like Deployment information, network Information.
            => No one can directly access the etcd database except kube-api server.(Only kube-api server can access etcd directly)
			=> NoSQL DB
			=> key Value Form
			=> Storage information about cluster.
		
	3) kube-scheduler:
	        => It check the health of all worker node first then decide which one is best for your application.
			=> It decides the right worker node for pod containers.

