Q) What are the services of worker nodes:
	1) Container Socket:
		=> dockerd: ( Not in use now days)
		=> containerd: 
		
		Redhat/IBM annous new socket:
		=> cri-io
		
	2) kubelet: 
			  => Its a agent of kubernetes master which need to run on each worker node. without kubelet kubernetes cannot control container host.
			  => It take instruction from kubernetes master and execute on worker node.
			  => It is responsible for all the activity on worker nodes.
		 
		  Flow(when kube-api request kubelet to create pod)
			=================================================
			kube-api (command/request to create container) => kubelet (request to container runtime engine(containerd) to create container) => containerd create pod.
            containerd(Send status of pod has been created) => kubelet(forwad this information to) => kube-api(forward to etcd) => etcd(store status in db)

	3) kube-proxy:
	     => Responsible for communication between pods.
	     => Manage your container traffic layer work.
		
